title: Teisseire Bastille Day Story Part1 1080x1920 FinalCut
18 September 2023
TeisseirePost 1
metaboytech ball
description:
Greetings, Esteemed Hydrators of the Universe,

The task before us may appear humble, but its implications are monumental. I present to you a container, a vessel, a chalice—commonly known as a "glass"—filled to the brim with nature's finest: water.

Just as WebXR explores realms beyond 2D boundaries, so does the act of drinking water nourish beyond mere physical sustenance. It revitalizes mind, body, and soul. A simple sip is a step, nay, a leap, into a new frontier of well-being.

1. **Grip the Reality**: Take hold of the glass. Feel its weight—this is the gravity of your mission. You're not merely lifting a glass; you are taking hold of a lifeline. As your fingers wrap around it, consider this your first handshake with vitality.

2. **Elevation is Key**: With the same audacity that took us to the moon, raise the glass towards your lips. Gravity may pull it down, but your spirit, my fellow hydrators, will lift it up.

3. **Pause for Democracy**: Before you sip, take a moment to appreciate the freedom in your choice. Much like a voter in a booth or a coder before a keyboard, this is your moment of power. Exercise it wisely.

4. **The Inauguration**: As the water meets your lips, let it cascade with grace and dignity onto your waiting palate. This is not merely a sip; it's the ceremonial ushering in of a hydrated new era.

5. **Executive Function**: Swallow. Feel the water's journey, much like our nation's history, from aspiration to realization. It travels down, a liquid interstate of unity, contributing to the greater good of the body. You have just ratified your own personal constitution of health.

6. **The Future is Now**: Place the glass back on the table. Let it rest, but know that this is not the end. Like our enduring Republic, it stands ready for the next cycle of renewal and refreshment.

And so, my fellow humans, you have completed an act simple in mechanics but profound in meaning. You've turned the act of drinking water into a symphony of purpose and a dance of existence.

Stay thirsty for greatness, but never for water.

---
If you interested in production background, more info:

Fact Sheet: European Year of Equal Opportunities for All
The European Commission has designated 2007 the European Year of Equal Opportunities for All. The aim is to promote the rights of everyone to equal treatment and a life free of discrimination, and to draw attention to the benefits of diversity. The European Union has already adopted far-reaching legislation which prohibits discrimination on the grounds of gender, racial or ethnic origin, religion or belief, age, disability and sexual orientation. In 2003, the European Commission launched the five-year campaign "For Diversity, Against Discrimination". The Year will introduce a bolder strategy and give further momentum to the EU-wide fight against discrimination with a year-long series of events and activities taking place both nationally and on a pan-European level. The launch of the Year will take place in Berlin on 30 January 2007 under the auspices of the German EU Presidency.
Aims:In 2000, the European Union adopted two very wide-ranging laws to prohibit discrimination based on gender, racial or ethnic origin, religion or belief, disability, age or sexual orientation. However, calling for equal rights and adopting laws to try and guarantee them is not enough to ensure that equal opportunities are enjoyed by everyone in practice. The benefits of diversity have to be shown to bring about a change in behaviour. The Year will promote equal opportunities and raise awareness about the rights of everyone to equal treatment, and the benefits of diversity. Non-discrimination is not only a moral argument -- diversity also makes economic sense. The Year will promote the benefits of diversity and establish that to benefit from the full wealth of skills, talent and ideas it is vital that everyone is included.
Thematic Focus:
Activities will need to provide a balanced treatment of all grounds of discrimination that are addressed at EU level (gender, racial or ethnic origin, religion or belief, disability, age or sexual orientation). In addition activities must be balanced in promoting the four designated objectives of the Year: 
Rights (raising awareness about and protecting rights) 
Representation (promoting the participation of all groups in society)

title: CASHLESS
description: Sooner or later we are approaching a new cash less world without money as we knew and our parents used to know. A cashless society describes an economic state whereby financial transactions are not conducted with money in the form of physical banknotes or coins, but rather through the transfer of digital information (usually an electronic representation of money) between the transacting parties. Is it a good thing or bad - we have multiple opinions and contrary views. title: LEGION
description:
United States Flag Code:
https://www.legion.org/flag/code

Thirteen equal horizontal stripes of red (top and bottom) alternating with white, with a blue rectangle in the canton (referred to specifically as the "union") bearing fifty small, white, five-pointed stars arranged in nine offset horizontal rows, where rows of six stars (top and bottom) alternate with rows of five stars. The 50 stars on the flag represent the 50 states of the United States of America, and the 13 stripes represent the thirteen British colonies that declared independence from the Kingdom of Great Britain, and became the first states in the U.S.

title: STARS
description: STARS - a 2 hours study how to play with path animation in blender. So you create the path, then you add taper and bevel objects, then you create a timeline animation changing bevel the end and the start position, do not forget to check the mapping. title: Voxel Builder - Prototype - Desktop Browser
description:
Voxel Builder - Web App Prototype

🌐 Platform: Desktop Browser
🛠️ Features:

Build your own voxel world with intuitive tools.
Easy extrusion for enhanced creativity.
Save and organize your own presets for later use.
Seamlessly import all presets with a click.
🔗 Proof of Concept (POC): https://xr.workwork.fun/111/

Furthermore, this experience stands out due to its support for the WebXR API. This enables you to immerse yourself in the voxel world through a first-person VR perspective. You have the ability to teleport, whether to the closest voxel surfaces or those that are distant. For a firsthand look, here's a demo recorded using the Oculus Browser on the Quest 2 device:

https://youtu.be/kyyI9nzjS8o

Dive in and explore the limitless possibilities of voxel world creation with Voxel Builder! Feedback and suggestions are highly appreciated. If you find this tool intriguing, don't forget to like, share, and subscribe for more updates.

title: Metaboy.tech: DEMOS
METABOY / AUDIO UTILS / Early Demos (IC - Immersive Collective)
description:
Yoall! How's going? 

In this video, I'm exploring the capabilities of my AudioUtils library, which is set to become a component of the Metaboy Demos project. Currently, I'm gathering additional audio probe data to generate a static waveform representation. Alongside this, the WebXR demo showcases a basic world powered by the RAPIER physics engine and features hand pose detection. For example, pinching your right hand will spawn extra cubes, while making a fist allows you to shoot a ball.

However, the shooting mechanism still needs fine-tuning. As of now, the aiming is a bit unpredictable, likely because the ball collides with the hand within the same collision/rigid system. It's a work in progress, so stay tuned for updates. You can test the demo in the Oculus Browser on the Quest 2.

Explore more: https://metaboy.tech/demos/au1/

Metaboy Demos
Immersive Collective on GitHub
https://github.com/Immersive-Collective

Immersive Collective Website
https://immersive-collective.org/

Kudos to Koshi Mazaki (https://github.com/koshimazaki) and his set of samples and loops I am allowed to play with.

title: Introducing YOLO.CX - Unleash Your Creativity
description:
Hey there,

Check this link!
https://gofund.me/6ef60c80

I'm Sylwester, and I'm reaching out to you from the heart of London. Recently, life took an unexpected turn as I found myself laid off from my job at Samsung Electronics. In the face of challenges, I've decided to channel my energy into something incredibly exciting and innovative – building an open web metaverse known as YOLO.CX.

Imagine a real-time 3D world where you can connect with friends and family seamlessly, regardless of where they are. YOLO.CX is more than just a project; it's a vision for a space where people can come together, share experiences, and create memories in a whole new way.

However, turning this vision into reality requires resources, and that's where I could use your support. The funds raised will be dedicated to crucial elements like hosting, storage, and a fast real-time database with a websocket solution. To ensure a smooth experience, we need to implement a cluster of at least 6 instances, which, as you can imagine, comes with a monthly cost that jumps from £50 to a few hundred pounds.

Here's where you come in – by supporting this crowdfunding campaign, you're not just helping me bring YOLO.CX to life; you're becoming a part of something groundbreaking. And I want to make it extra special for those who contribute.

Why should you join us?

Be among the first citizens of YOLO.CX!
Shape the early stages of the metaverse and witness its growth.
Play a crucial role in fostering innovation and connection in the digital realm.

I'm asking for your support, no matter how big or small, to make YOLO.CX a reality. Together, we can create a space that goes beyond the ordinary and explores new frontiers on the open web.

Ready to embark on this journey with me? Contribute and be part of the YOLO.CX community.
Thank you for being a part of this adventure!

Cheers,
Sylwester
